    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Preserve Aalto's Rooms</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter by Allan E Goodman explains that when Institute of International Education sold its conference center at UN Plaza it was group's understanding that Alvar Aalto rooms would be preserved (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Aalto Room May Be Shown the Door'' (Sept. 14): The Aalto rooms at 809 United Nations Plaza are an architectural gem. As the organization that has used and maintained this conference center in a building that we owned for nearly four decades, and in which we continue to have our headquarters, the Institute of International Education wants the Aalto design preserved in its current space.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Aalto Room May Be Shown the Door'' (Sept. 14): The Aalto rooms at 809 United Nations Plaza are an architectural gem. As the organization that has used and maintained this conference center in a building that we owned for nearly four decades, and in which we continue to have our headquarters, the Institute of International Education wants the Aalto design preserved in its current space.</p>
        <p>When we sold the building in December 1998, it was our understanding that the conference center would remain. It is our sincere hope that the new owners will preserve this unique architectural treasure in the location for which it was created.</p>
        <p>ALLAN E. GOODMAN  President, Institute  of International Education  New York</p>
      </block>
